Definition: a school of painters who used a technique of painting with tiny dots of pure colors that would blend in the viewer's eye
Example: developed by Georges Seurat and his followers late in 19th century France
Synonyms: adj, all, patterned, pointillistic, school, artistic_movement, a, of, painters, who, used, technique, painting, with, tiny, dots, pure, colors, that, would, blend, in, the, viewer, s, eye, developed, by, Georges, Seurat, and, his, followers, late, th, century, France
Category: noun.group
